        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  positive family history of type II diabetes mellitus and/or metabolic
             syndrome(AHA/NHLBI criteria).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  any therapy related to metabolic syndrome (that is antihypertensive, anti diabetic,
             antilipemic drugs);

          -  age < 18 years or >50 years;

          -  previously diagnosed hypertension or immediate need for antihypertensive therapy
             (BPâ‰¥160/100);

          -  diabetes mellitus (ADA criteria);

          -  obesity (BMI>30Kg/m2);

          -  Continuative use of NSAIDs, magnesium or vitamin supplements;

          -  Hypermagnesaemia;

          -  Previous cardio- or cerebrovascular events;

          -  chronic kidney or liver or inflammatory or neoplastic disease;

          -  gastrointestinal dysfunction with hypomotility;

          -  active smoke (>5 cigarettes per day);

          -  Impossibility to give informed consent.
